<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-82-0992 </DOCNO><TEXT>In a speech to the International Gas Union's World Gas Conference, USPresident Reagan said the Congress should remove the controls of naturalgas and provide more efficient pipeline transportation. Higher naturalgas prices, while harmful to consumers, would encourage more explorationand production. Deregulation of natural gas prices began in 1985 butmuch of the older supplies of gas remains under price controls. Reagansaid the US could significantly reduce dependence on foreign oil by makinggreater use of its abundant natural gas reserves.</TEXT></DOC>